      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's more complex than just acid buildup, though the acidity is the sensation you feel, which is what makes the burning feel so intense. While the buildup itself is what causes the acute discomfort, the body's cleanup crew is always at work, even if it feels slow. You can't instantly stop the metabolic process, but incorporating active recovery, like a light jog or walking, after a sprint session can actually help speed up the clearance process. This gentle movement helps shuttle those lactate molecules away from the fatigued muscle fibers.",
      "source": "target",
